	<refmeta>
		<refentrytitle>lexi</refentrytitle>
		<manvolnum>1</manvolnum>
	</refmeta>

	<refnamediv id="name">
		<refname>lexi</refname>
		<refpurpose>Lexical analyser tool</refpurpose>
	</refnamediv>

	<refsynopsisdiv id="synopsis">
		<cmdsynopsis>
			<command>lexi</command>

			<arg choice="opt"><option>-a</option></arg>
			<arg choice="opt"><option>-t</option> <replaceable>token-prefix</replaceable></arg>
			<arg choice="opt"><option>-p</option> <replaceable>token-prefix</replaceable></arg>
			<arg choice="opt"><option>-i</option> <replaceable>interface-prefix</replaceable></arg>
			<arg choice="opt"><option>-l</option> <replaceable>lang</replaceable></arg>

			<sbr/>

			<arg choice="plain" rep="repeat"><replaceable>input-file</replaceable></arg>
			<arg choice="opt"   rep="repeat"><replaceable>output-file</replaceable></arg>
		</cmdsynopsis>

		<cmdsynopsis>
			<command>lexi</command>

			<group choice="req">
				<arg choice="plain">-h</arg>
				<arg choice="plain">-v</arg>
			</group>
		</cmdsynopsis>
	</refsynopsisdiv>

	<refsection id="description">
		<title>Description</title>

		<para><application>Lexi</application> translates a description of a
			lexical analyser, <emphasis>input-file</emphasis>,
			into code implementing that analyser.
			This is output into the
			<filename>output-file</filename> argument, if present,
			or the standard output otherwise.</para>

		<para>Both <replaceable>input-file</replaceable> and
			<replaceable>output-file</replaceable> may be given as
			<quote>-</quote> for standard input and standard output
			respectivley.
			These are language-specific (see the <option>-l</option>
			option), and may represent multiple files.</para>
	</refsection>

	<refsection id="options">
		<title>Options</title>

		<variablelist>
			<varlistentry>
				<term><option>-a</option></term>
				<listitem>Disables assertions in the output code.
					These are enabled by default.</listitem>
			</varlistentry>

			<varlistentry>
				<term><option>-t</option> <replaceable>token-prefix</replaceable></term>
				<listitem>Causes <command>lexi</command> to use
						<replaceable>string</replaceable> as a prefix
						for its generated lexical tokens. The default is
						<literal>lex_</literal>.</listitem>
			</varlistentry>

			<varlistentry>
				<term><option>-p</option> <replaceable>lexi-prefix</replaceable></term>
				<listitem>Causes <command>lexi</command> to use
						<replaceable>string</replaceable> as a prefix
						for its generated internal symbols. The default is
						<literal>lexi_</literal>.</listitem>
			</varlistentry>

			<varlistentry>
				<term><option>-i</option> <replaceable>interface-prefix</replaceable></term>
				<listitem>Causes <command>lexi</command> to use
						<replaceable>string</replaceable> as a prefix
						for its generated interface. The default is
						<literal>lexi_</literal>.</listitem>
			</varlistentry>

			<varlistentry>
				<term><option>-l</option> <replaceable>lang</replaceable></term>
				<listitem>
					<para>The <option>-l</option> specifies the output language
						for the generated lexer.
						The <replaceable>input-file</replaceable>s
						and <replaceable>output-file</replaceable>s
						are specific to each language.
						The language is currently one of:</para>

					<table>
						<col align="left"/>
						<col align="right"/>
						<col align="left"/>
						<col align="left"/>

						<thead>
							<tr>
								<th>Language</th>
								<th colspan="2" align="center">Action</th>
								<th>Description</th>
							</tr>
						</thead>

						<tbody>
							<tr>
								<td><literal>C90</literal> (default)</td>
								<td role="input"><filename>.lxi</filename>, <filename>.lct</filename></td>
								<td role="output"><filename>.c</filename>,   <filename>.h</filename></td>
								<td>ISO C90</td>
							</tr>
							<tr>
								<td><literal>C99</literal></td>
								<td role="input"><filename>.lxi</filename>, <filename>.lct</filename></td>
								<td role="output"><filename>.c</filename>,   <filename>.h</filename></td>
								<td>ISO C99</td>
							</tr>
							<tr>
								<td><literal>dot</literal></td>
								<td role="input"><filename>.lxi</filename></td>
								<td role="output"><filename>.dot</filename></td>
								<td>Graphviz <filename>.dot</filename> format</td>
							</tr>
							<tr>
								<td><literal>test</literal></td>
								<td role="input"><filename>.lxi</filename></td>
								<td role="output na" align="center">&ndash;</td>
								<td>For testing lexers</td>
							</tr>
						</tbody>
					</table>

					<para>The language is case-insensitive.</para>
				</listitem>
			</varlistentry>

			<varlistentry>
				<term>
					<option>-v</option>
				</term>
				<listitem>
					<para>Causes <application>Lexi</application> to print its
						version number.</para>
				</listitem>
			</varlistentry>

			<varlistentry>
				<term>
					<option>-h</option>
				</term>
				<listitem>
					<para>Causes <application>Lexi</application> to print
						command-line usage help.</para>
				</listitem>
			</varlistentry>
		</variablelist>

		<para>For further details of the options available and a reference
			to the format for files see the <citetitle pubwork="article">The
			Lexi users' Guide</citetitle>.</para>
